originalText.text: Best cleaners and seamstress in Chelsea!  Jason and Amanda are amazing!  They do a wonderful job cleaning and rejuvenating my dress shirts so I always look classy and dapper.  Amanda must have trained on Savile Row as she alters my outfits perfectly. The whole staff are always sweet and sincere with an affable, inviting demeanor.  They add a warm touch to the neighborhood so I highly recommend Eco Highline Cleaners.

originalText.text:
Dishonest and incompetent. Always be careful with the receipt you receive, they charged my credit card without my authorization. The quality of the alteration work is also pretty bad -see attached proof.

I came here feeling excited to try their service in the neighborhood and left extremely disappointed not by just the service but also the way they conducted business. I was quoted and charged for certain amount and when I received my dress (which came late btw), they charged me double the amount which I never agreed to.

I tried to resolve the issue and the owner just yelled on the phone, it was very disrespectful and unprofessional.

All in all, save yourself a hassle and go to other eco laundry cleaners. I wouldn't recommend anyone to use their service.

originalText.text: One of the best. I had a white button down shirt with neon stains that I took to another cleaner that they didn't get out. I brought it to Eco Highline and they got all the stains out! It looked brand new. I have also had tailoring done and they do a fantastic job at a reasonable price! Only use them now.

originalText.text: A bum threw coffee at my nice Burberry scarf near Times Square. The folks here were able to get rid of that coffee stain and made it look brand new! I will definitely return here for future dry cleaning needs.
